==English==

===Noun===
'''positive transition'''  
#(Advertising) one of four archetypal [[dramatic structure|dramatic structures]] of commercials characterized by an emotionally neutral beginning with an enormous leap in positive emotions generated by seeing the branded product in use.
#:''The SUV ad featuring an ordinary man walking away from his ordinary home on his way to work and then shows him feeling like a daredevil behind the wheel of his SUV utilizes the [[dramatic structure]] known as a '''positive transition'''.''
#(Advertising) a narrative structure used in commercials known as “supporting actor-type” advertising.



